{
  "texts": [
    "In multiclass tasks like BANKING77, LMs sometimes invent new labels or produce minor syntactic variations (balance-not-updated vs. balance_not_updated).",
    "Thorough prompt ablations, or per-model prompt adaptation, might reduce these inconsistencies but can be prohibitively expensive at scale.",
    "LMs tend to handle classification outputs better than continuous-valued regressions (e.g., sentiment",
    "Information Retrieval Numeric labeling tasks demand robust domain logic; simple zero-shot prompts often fail to capture precise numerical relations.",
    "FNXL: even DEEPSEEK R1 only achieves 0.057 F1, missing most numeric labels in financial tables."
  ]
}